<TITLE> Hasina warns ministers of actions over charges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina warned the ministers on Sunday of actions if allegations were found against them, according to the commerce minister. "If any allegation is found against anyone action will be taken against him/her," Faruq Khan quoted Hasina as telling them. "The prime minister has given directives to the ministers and state ministers to get all documents of their respective ministries in seven days," he told reporters at the Secretariat after the meeting that started at 10:40am. The new head of government then started meeting with the secretaries to the ministries and divisions shortly before 1pm. She will be briefed on the state of things by the top civil servants. Faruq, the commerce minister, said from now the prime minister would often attend her office at the Secretariat. The meeting of the cabinet members would be held on Monday at the Cabinet Division conference room. Hasina's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters the cabinet would meet on Mondays. During the caretaker government regime, the cabinet meeting was held on Sundays, while the past four-party alliance government would call cabinet meeting on Mondays. bd
